{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result"]]},"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"API Collection","modules":[{"name":"HMResult"}],"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Mapping Methods"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"General-transformation","level":5,"type":"heading","text":"General transformation"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Transforming a value, by applying a function to it using dot syntax, is sometimes an easier-to-read way to write code, and probably ought to be available on "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"every type"}]},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["func transform<Transformed, Error>(","  _ transform: (Self) throws(Error) -> Transformed",") throws(Error) -> Transformed {","  try transform(self)","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"But that’s not specific to ","type":"text"},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and is not included in this package.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"could","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" restrict the transformation to require mapping similar types of "},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s, such as"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Result<Int, Never>","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" ➡️ "},{"code":"Result<String, any Error>","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"That would look like this:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["func transform<NewSuccess, NewFailure, Error>(","  _ transform: (Self) throws(Error) -> Result<NewSuccess, NewFailure>",") throws(Error) -> Result<NewSuccess, NewFailure> {","  try transform(self)","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even with this new restriction, the possibilities are so vast in what can be accomplished there, that it’s not worth creating a function for. And so again, this "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"type":"text","text":" is not included in this package either."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"flatMap","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"flatMap"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is the closest to a general-purpose "},{"code":"transform","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method that this package works with. The capabilities are different in only two respects:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"text":"‘s’ ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"text":" closure operates only on a wrapped value, instead of an entire ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"text":" cannot modify the wrapped error type.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The “","type":"text"},{"code":"flat","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"” in ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" refers to the way that it introduces no more “nesting” than the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" represented before transformation. For example,","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["Result<String, Never>.flatMap"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":", when supplied with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"type":"text","text":" closure returning type"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["Result<Int, Never>"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":", will return"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["Result<Int, Never>"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":", as opposed to an “unflattened”"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["Result<Result<Int, Never>, Never>"]},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/flatMap(_:)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"As documented below","type":"text"}],"overridingTitle":"As documented below"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"type":"text","text":" will not throw an error when the transformed "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":" is a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"failure"},{"type":"text","text":", but it will throw an error if the transformation throws an error."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/result\/flatMap(_:)","type":"reference"},{"text":" nearly gets ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" right, but it does not incorporate throwing an error. This version should be deprecated.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"flatMapAndMergeError","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"flatMapAndMergeError"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is a special case of ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". If ","type":"text"},{"code":"transform","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" throws the untransformed ","type":"text"},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" type, the error can be forwarded into the transformed wrapper type, rather than being thrown from ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both forms are useful. Naming this differently than "},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is necessary because it would not be enough, for the compiler, to just add "},{"code":"try","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in front of another "},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" overload."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"map","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"map"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The only difference between "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":" is that map’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"type":"text","text":" closure returns a wrapped value, not a wrapper. Thusly, no “flattening” is necessary."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/result\/map(_:)"},{"text":" nearly gets ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":" right, but it does not incorporate throwing an error. This version should be deprecated.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"mapAndMergeError","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"mapAndMergeError"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is to ","type":"text"},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMapAndMergeError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is to ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"flatMapFailure","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"flatMapFailure"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the same idea as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"text":", except, with a transformation of the wrapper’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Failure"},{"text":" type, rather than its ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Value"},{"text":" type.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As we’ve seen above with ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the standard library nearly gets this right, under the problematic* name ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/result\/flatMapError(_:)","type":"reference"},{"text":", but it does not incorporate throwing an error. It ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"should"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", for completeness, but does anyone need that? 🤔 (It won’t be included in this package until we hear that they do.)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"* It’s problematic because the failure type, while restricted to be an error, is called "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Failure"},{"type":"text","text":", not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Error"},{"type":"text","text":". And it’s not clear whether you’re mapping a failure enumeration case, or an error occurring from the transformation closure."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"mapFailure","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"mapFailure"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMapFailure"},{"type":"text","text":" as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":" is to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"mapFailureToSuccess","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"mapFailureToSuccess"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This idea only works when the "},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" type is going to be “removed”, which is represented by "},{"code":"Never","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". So, there’s no point in offering a "},{"code":"flatMapFailureToSuccess","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", as "},{"code":"Result.failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s can’t be created with if their "},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"code":"Never","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"mapFailureToSuccessAndErrorToFailure","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"mapFailureToSuccessAndErrorToFailure"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a niche type of error mapping operation."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It’s similar to the two “","type":"text"},{"code":"…AndMergeError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"” methods in that an error thrown from transforming will become a ","type":"text"},{"code":"failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"But it’s dissimilar in that while the error thrown ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"can"}]},{"text":" be ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Failure"},{"text":", there’s no requirement of that (and it’s likely to be a rare case). So, calling this ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mapFailureToSuccessAndMergeError"},{"text":" would not generally be accurate.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Mapping-Methods"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/flatMap(_:)","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/flatMapAndMergeError(_:)","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/map(_:)","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/mapAndMergeError(_:)","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/mapFailureToSuccess(_:)","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/mapFailureToSuccessAndErrorToFailure(_:)"],"anchor":"Topics"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":[